snippet.title: Over The Counter Swap Of Notes Ends Now

localized.description:
The exchange of old 500 and 1,000 rupee notes in banks and post offices will be stopped starting midnight, the government has said. People will still be able to go to banks to deposit their old bills in their bank accounts and withdraw under the current limits.

Watch more videos: http://www.ndtv.com/video?yt
